Author: MACDONALD
Vol / Page: 142
Edition:
Quote: The following wool trade terms are explained:- MUSHY WOOL: Shows no pronounced staple; from badly bred or old sheep. SHAFTINESS: A wool with a pronounced staple. SLIPE WOOL: Taken from the skins of sheep; not shorn wool.
